<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="C" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Confused" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Confused,</orth> indistinguishably mixed, disordered, indistinct: <cit><quote>sounds c.</quote> <bibl n="shak. h5 3.0" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 III Chor.</bibl></cit> <bibl n="shak. h5 3.0" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 III Chor.</bibl> <cit><quote>howls c.</quote> <bibl n="shak. h5 3.3.39" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 3, 39</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a din c.</quote> <bibl n="shak. cor 3.3.20" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. III, 3, 20</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>c. cries,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tit 2.3.102" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. II, 3, 102</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>I never heard a passion so c.</quote> <bibl n="shak. mv 2.8.12" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. II, 8, 12</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>c. wrong,</quote> <bibl n="shak. jn 5.2.23" default="NO" valid="yes">John V, 2, 23</bibl></cit> (no more to be distinguished from right). <cit><quote>c. events,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mac 2.3.63" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. II, 3, 63</bibl></cit> (i. e. disorders, revolutions). <cit><quote>'tis here, but yet c.</quote> <bibl n="shak. oth 2.1.320" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. II, 1, 320</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>